==English==
===Etymology===
French [[amplifier]], Latin [[amplificare]].  See  [[Ample]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæmp.lɪ.faɪ/

===Transitive Verb===
# To render larger, more extended, or more intense, and the  like;&mdash;used especially of telescopes, microscopes, etc.
# (Rhetorical) To enlarge by addition or discussion; to treat copiously by adding particulars, illustrations, etc.; to expand; to make much of.
